cs.AR, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.ET, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) because it proposes a DNN architecture with a precision-adaptable FPGA soft core. It is also likely to belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) because it deals with DNNs and their optimization. Additionally, it may belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.ET (Emerging Technologies) because it discusses the trade-offs between DNN performance and hardware resources.
